---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
const articles = [
  {
    slug: 'how-much-should-hvac-company-spend-on-marketing-2026',
    trade: 'HVAC · Revenue Diagnostics',
    title: 'How Much Should an HVAC Company Spend on Marketing in 2026?',
    preview: "Most owners are spending $8K–$15K/month without knowing their cost per booked job. Here's the actual math — benchmarks, a 5-step budget formula, and the three places HVAC companies silently leak marketing budget.",
    date: 'Mar 16, 2026',
    readTime: 11,
    img: 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1621905251918-48416bd8575a?w=800&q=75',
    imgAlt: 'HVAC technician servicing rooftop AC unit',
    pills: ['$340 avg cost/job', '7-10% revenue typical', '3 leak patterns'],
    featured: true,
  },
  {
    slug: 'why-hvac-csrs-are-losing-you-300k-per-year',
    trade: 'HVAC · Pipeline Systems',
    title: 'Why Your HVAC CSRs Are Losing You $300K/Year (Without Anyone Noticing)',
    preview: "Your phones are answered. Your CSRs are friendly. And you're still losing $300K a year in calls that never became booked jobs. Here's exactly where it's happening and the three fixes that recover most of it.",
    date: 'Mar 17, 2026',
    readTime: 12,
    img: 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1521791136064-7986c2920216?w=800&q=75',
    imgAlt: 'CSR on phone handling inbound service calls',
    pills: ['68% avg answer rate', '$160K/month gap', '3 specific fixes'],
    featured: false,
  },
];
---
<Layout
  title="Insights — Growth Research for HVAC, Roofing & Plumbing | Built on Tenth"
  description="Research, benchmarks, and analysis from studying hundreds of home service companies. What the most profitable HVAC, roofing, and plumbing operators do differently."
  active="insights"
>

<style>
.insights-hero { padding: 140px 48px 80px; position: relative; overflow: hidden; }
.insights-hero-glow { position: absolute; inset: 0; background: radial-gradient(ellipse 60% 60% at 20% 50%, rgba(0,196,154,0.05) 0%, transparent 60%); }
.insights-hero-inner { position: relative; z-index: 1; max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto; display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 80px; align-items: end; }
.insights-hero h1 { font-family: var(--serif); font-size: clamp(34px, 5vw, 58px); font-weight: 400; line-height: 1.1; letter-spacing: -0.02em; margin-bottom: 20px; }
.insights-hero h1 em { font-style: italic; color: var(--teal); }
.pillar-tabs { display: flex; gap: 8px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
.pt { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 10px; font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--ink3); background: var(--bg3); border: 1px solid var(--rule2); padding: 7px 14px; border-radius: 3px; text-decoration: none; transition: all 0.2s; }
.pt:hover, .pt.active { color: var(--teal); border-color: var(--teal4); background: var(--teal3); }
.featured-article { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 380px; gap: 0; background: var(--bg2); border: 1px solid var(--rule2); border-radius: 6px; overflow: hidden; text-decoration: none; color: inherit; transition: border-color 0.25s, transform 0.25s; margin-bottom: 1px; }
.featured-article:hover { border-color: rgba(0,196,154,0.35); transform: translateY(-2px); }
.fa-body { padding: 40px; display: flex; flex-direction: column; justify-content: space-between; }
.fa-meta { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 12px; margin-bottom: 18px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
.fa-trade { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 9.5px; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.12em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--teal); }
.fa-date, .fa-read { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 9.5px; color: var(--ink3); letter-spacing: 0.06em; }
.fa-title { font-family: var(--serif); font-size: clamp(22px, 3vw, 30px); font-weight: 400; line-height: 1.22; margin-bottom: 16px; }
.fa-preview { font-size: 14.5px; color: var(--ink2); line-height: 1.72; font-weight: 300; margin-bottom: 20px; flex: 1; }
.fa-pills { display: flex; gap: 8px; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-bottom: 24px; }
.fa-pill { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 9.5px; font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: 0.08em; color: var(--ink3); background: var(--bg4); border: 1px solid var(--rule); padding: 4px 10px; border-radius: 3px; }
.fa-cta { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 11px; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--teal); display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px; transition: gap 0.2s; }
.featured-article:hover .fa-cta { gap: 10px; }
.fa-img { position: relative; overflow: hidden; background: var(--bg3); min-height: 320px; }
.fa-img img { width: 100%; height: 100%; object-fit: cover; filter: grayscale(20%) brightness(0.72); transition: transform 0.6s var(--ease); display: block; }
.featured-article:hover .fa-img img { transform: scale(1.04); }
.fa-img::before { content: ''; position: absolute; inset: 0; z-index: 1; background: rgba(0,196,154,0.06); pointer-events: none; }
.fa-img-badge { position: absolute; top: 16px; left: 16px; z-index: 2; font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 9px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--bg); background: var(--teal); padding: 4px 10px; border-radius: 3px; }
.articles-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); gap: 1px; background: var(--rule); border: 1px solid var(--rule); border-radius: 6px; overflow: hidden; }
.article-card { background: var(--bg2); display: flex; flex-direction: column; text-decoration: none; color: inherit; transition: background 0.25s; overflow: hidden; }
.article-card:hover { background: var(--bg3); }
.ac-img { width: 100%; height: 200px; overflow: hidden; position: relative; background: var(--bg3); }
.ac-img img { width: 100%; height: 100%; object-fit: cover; filter: grayscale(20%) brightness(0.72); transition: transform 0.5s var(--ease); display: block; }
.article-card:hover .ac-img img { transform: scale(1.04); }
.ac-img::before { content: ''; position: absolute; inset: 0; z-index: 1; background: rgba(0,196,154,0.06); pointer-events: none; }
.ac-body { padding: 28px; display: flex; flex-direction: column; flex: 1; }
.ac-meta { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 12px; margin-bottom: 14px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
.ac-trade { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 9.5px; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.12em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--teal); }
.ac-date { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 9.5px; color: var(--ink3); letter-spacing: 0.06em; }
.ac-title { font-family: var(--serif); font-size: 20px; font-weight: 400; line-height: 1.28; margin-bottom: 12px; }
.ac-preview { font-size: 13.5px; color: var(--ink2); line-height: 1.65; font-weight: 300; margin-bottom: 16px; flex: 1; }
.ac-pills { display: flex; gap: 6px; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-bottom: 18px; }
.ac-pill { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 9px; font-weight: 500; color: var(--ink3); background: var(--bg4); border: 1px solid var(--rule); padding: 3px 8px; border-radius: 3px; }
.ac-read { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 10px; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--teal); display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 5px; transition: gap 0.2s; }
.article-card:hover .ac-read { gap: 8px; }
.article-card.soon { opacity: 0.4; pointer-events: none; }
.ac-coming { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 9px; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--ink3); background: var(--bg4); border: 1px solid var(--rule); padding: 3px 8px; border-radius: 3px; width: fit-content; margin-top: auto; }
.nl-prompt { background: rgba(0,196,154,0.04); border: 1px solid rgba(0,196,154,0.22); border-radius: 6px; padding: 28px 32px; margin-top: 36px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; gap: 24px; }
.nl-prompt-text h3 { font-family: var(--serif); font-size: 19px; font-weight: 400; margin-bottom: 5px; }
.nl-prompt-text p { font-size: 13.5px; color: var(--ink2); font-weight: 300; line-height: 1.6; }
.nl-prompt-form { display: flex; gap: 10px; flex-shrink: 0; }
.nl-prompt-input { background: var(--bg3); border: 1px solid var(--rule2); border-radius: 4px; padding: 11px 16px; font-family: var(--sans); font-size: 13.5px; color: var(--ink); outline: none; transition: border-color 0.2s; width: 220px; }
.nl-prompt-input::placeholder { color: var(--ink3); }
.nl-prompt-input:focus { border-color: rgba(0,196,154,0.5); }
@media (max-width: 960px) {
  .insights-hero { padding: 100px 20px 60px; }
  .insights-hero-inner { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 28px; }
  .featured-article { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  .fa-img { min-height: 220px; order: -1; }
  .fa-body { padding: 24px 20px; }
  .articles-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  .nl-prompt { flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start; }
  .nl-prompt-form { flex-direction: column; width: 100%; }
  .nl-prompt-input { width: 100%; }
}
</style>

<div class="insights-hero">
  <div class="insights-hero-glow"></div>
  <div class="insights-hero-inner">
    <div>
      <div class="dispatch-label">Research &amp; Analysis</div>
      <h1>What the most profitable companies<br><em>actually do differently.</em></h1>
      <p class="sec-p">Every article is built on data from analyzing real HVAC, roofing, and plumbing companies. No opinion pieces. No generic advice. Just patterns from the numbers.</p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <p style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:0.12em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--ink3);margin-bottom:14px">Filter by trade</p>
      <div class="pillar-tabs">
        <a href="/insights" class="pt active">All</a>
        <a href="/insights" class="pt">HVAC</a>
        <a href="/insights" class="pt">Roofing</a>
        <a href="/insights" class="pt">Plumbing</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="wrap">
  <div class="inner">
    <div class="rule-label"><span class="section-tag">Published Research</span></div>

    <a href="/insights/how-much-should-hvac-company-spend-on-marketing-2026" class="featured-article reveal">
      <div class="fa-body">
        <div>
          <div class="fa-meta">
            <span class="fa-trade">HVAC &middot; Revenue Diagnostics</span>
            <span class="fa-date">Mar 16, 2026</span>
            <span class="fa-read">11 min read</span>
          </div>
          <div class="fa-title">How Much Should an HVAC Company Spend on Marketing in 2026?</div>
          <p class="fa-preview">Most owners are spending $8K to $15K a month without knowing their cost per booked job. Here is the actual math, benchmarks, a 5-step budget formula, and the three places HVAC companies silently leak marketing budget.</p>
          <div class="fa-pills">
            <span class="fa-pill">$340 avg cost/job</span>
            <span class="fa-pill">7-10% revenue typical</span>
            <span class="fa-pill">3 leak patterns</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <span class="fa-cta">Read Article &rarr;</span>
      </div>
      <div class="fa-img">
        <span class="fa-img-badge">Featured</span>
        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1621905251918-48416bd8575a?w=800&q=75" alt="HVAC technician servicing rooftop AC unit" loading="lazy" />
      </div>
    </a>

    <div class="articles-grid" style="margin-top:1px">
      <a href="/insights/why-hvac-csrs-are-losing-you-300k-per-year" class="article-card reveal">
        <div class="ac-img">
          <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1521791136064-7986c2920216?w=800&q=75" alt="CSR on phone handling inbound calls" loading="lazy" />
        </div>
        <div class="ac-body">
          <div class="ac-meta">
            <span class="ac-trade">HVAC &middot; Pipeline Systems</span>
            <span class="ac-date">Mar 17, 2026</span>
          </div>
          <div class="ac-title">Why Your HVAC CSRs Are Losing You $300K/Year (Without Anyone Noticing)</div>
          <p class="ac-preview">Your phones are answered. Your CSRs are friendly. And you are still losing $300K a year in calls that never became booked jobs. Here is exactly where it is happening and the three fixes that recover most of it.</p>
          <div class="ac-pills">
            <span class="ac-pill">68% avg answer rate</span>
            <span class="ac-pill">$160K/month gap</span>
            <span class="ac-pill">3 specific fixes</span>
          </div>
          <span class="ac-read">Read Article &rarr;</span>
        </div>
      </a>

      <div class="article-card soon">
        <div class="ac-img" style="background:var(--bg3);min-height:200px"></div>
        <div class="ac-body">
          <div class="ac-meta"><span class="ac-trade">Roofing &middot; Lead Sources</span></div>
          <div class="ac-title">Why Angi Leads Feel Like Garbage (And What Roofing Companies Do Instead)</div>
          <p class="ac-preview">Angi leads have a 12-18% close rate industry-wide. But some roofing companies close 35% of them. The difference is what happens in the first 4 minutes after the call comes in.</p>
          <div class="ac-coming">Coming soon</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="nl-prompt">
      <div class="nl-prompt-text">
        <h3>Get every article the day it publishes.</h3>
        <p>Subscribe to the Weekly Growth Report. One insight every Tuesday. Free.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="nl-prompt-form">
        <input type="email" class="nl-prompt-input" placeholder="your@email.com" id="insights-email" />
        <button class="cta-filled" style="cursor:pointer;white-space:nowrap" id="insights-submit">Subscribe Free</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<script>
  document.getElementById('insights-submit').addEventListener('click', async () => {
    const inp = document.getElementById('insights-email');
    const btn = document.getElementById('insights-submit');
    if (!inp.value.includes('@')) {
      inp.style.borderColor = 'rgba(240,64,64,0.55)';
      inp.focus();
      return;
    }
    btn.textContent = 'Subscribing...';
    btn.disabled = true;
    try {
      const res = await fetch('/api/subscribe', {
        method: 'POST',
        headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
        body: JSON.stringify({ email: inp.value.trim(), source: 'insights-page' }),
      });
      const data = await res.json();
      if (data.success) {
        btn.textContent = 'Subscribed';
        btn.style.background = '#22D37A';
        inp.disabled = true;
      } else {
        btn.textContent = 'Try again';
        btn.disabled = false;
      }
    } catch {
      btn.textContent = 'Try again';
      btn.disabled = false;
    }
  });
</script>
</Layout>
